Package: contsurvplot
Type: Package
Title: Visualize the Effect of a Continuous Variable on a Time-To-Event Outcome
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Robin", "Denz", , "robin.denz@rub.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Robin Denz <robin.denz@rub.de>
Description: A package containing multiple plot functions to graphically display the
	causal effect of a continuous variable on a time-to-event outcome. Those functions
	include a heatmap, survival time quantile plots, restricted mean survival
	time plots and a color graded survival curve. Allows confounder-adjustment.
License: GPL (>= 3)
URL: https://github.com/RobinDenz1/contsurvplot
BugReports: https://github.com/RobinDenz1/contsurvplot/issues
Imports:
	ggplot2 (>= 3.0.0),
	rlang,
	riskRegression,
	survival
Suggests:
	adjustedCurves,
	dplyr,
	pammtools
Contact: <robin.denz@rub.de>
Encoding: UTF-8
